## Research Experience
* **Graduate Researcher**, African Institute for Mathematical Sciences (AIMS) | 2023 – Present
  * Developed a novel **hybrid Minkowski-Log-Cosh loss function** to enhance LSTM robustness against outliers in time series forecasting.
  * Applied LSTM models to predict malaria case incidence using 10-year public health data (2013-2023), demonstrating improved accuracy in noisy epidemiological datasets.
  * Implemented robust deep learning pipelines for time series analysis with applications in public health forecasting.
* **Undergraduate Researcher**, Université de Kara | 2021 – 2022
  * Designed and implemented Artificial Neural Network (ANN) models for agricultural yield prediction, integrating climate, soil, and environmental variables.
  * Conducted research evaluating the socio-economic impact of online learning during the COVID-19 pandemic on university students.
  * Performed comprehensive feature sensitivity analysis to identify and rank key drivers of crop productivity.

